Adv Dali Mpofu, for suspended public protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane, says they will call President Cyril Ramaphosa to testify at the impeachment hearings — or, if he fails to appear, summon him before parliament. “It looks like we might even have to call other former presidents,” he said. Listen: This as parliament continues with  Mkhwebane’s impeachment proceedings. The hearing is in its fourth day on Thursday and is determining whether Mkhwebane is fit to hold office. TimesLIVE